rameters of liquid\n$^4$He such as the intrinsic linewidth $\\alpha_2$ (which sets the atomic\nkinetic energy $\\langle K\\rangle\\sim\\alpha_2$) in the normal liquid and the\nBose-Einstein condensate parameter $n_0$ in the superfluid phase. The extracted\n$\\alpha_2$ values agree well with previous measurements, independently of which\n$R_i(Q,y)$ is used to analyze the data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jul 2016 02:29:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-21"}
