ot passing through the triple point and\nentering the B2 solid phase. This transition leads to a discontinuity with 4.6%\nvolume collapse, about four times greater than the same B1-B2 transition at\nzero temperature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jul 2016 11:42:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-07"}
